{
  "video_id": "hs3piaN4b5I",
  "title": "Flexbox vs. CSS Grid â€” Which is Better?",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 160.0,
      "end_time": 1810.0,
      "text": "- One of the biggest questions people ask"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 1810.0,
      "end_time": 4160.0,
      "text": "when they first learn about CSS Grid is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 4160.0,
      "end_time": 6800.0,
      "text": "\"Hey, does this replace Flexbox?"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 6800.0,
      "end_time": 10050.0,
      "text": "\"Should I use Grid instead of Flexbox?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 10050.0,
      "end_time": 13200.0,
      "text": "No, that's not really how\nthings are gonna work."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 13200.0,
      "end_time": 16790.0,
      "text": "So, Grid has been\ninvented to do things that"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 16790.0,
      "end_time": 19520.0,
      "text": "Flexbox couldn't do, and Flexbox is still"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 19520.0,
      "end_time": 23190.0,
      "text": "a great tool for us to use to\ndo things that Grid can't do."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 23190.0,
      "end_time": 25670.0,
      "text": "And we're also gonna use\na lot of the other parts"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 25670.0,
      "end_time": 28260.0,
      "text": "of CSS that we've used for\nlayout for a long time."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 28260.0,
      "end_time": 29730.0,
      "text": "Floats, for example, there'll be"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 29730.0,
      "end_time": 31660.0,
      "text": "plenty of times to use a float."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 32694.000000000004,
      "end_time": 36960.0,
      "text": "And flow, the way the\nweb pages get laid out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 36960.0,
      "end_time": 39100.0,
      "text": "the way it's always been before CSS"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 39100.0,
      "end_time": 42320.0,
      "text": "actually was invented,\nthe way content flows"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 42320.0,
      "end_time": 44240.0,
      "text": "down the page in a block direction"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 44240.0,
      "end_time": 46410.0,
      "text": "or an in-line direction, these are all"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 46410.0,
      "end_time": 48520.0,
      "text": "parts of a larger picture that we'll"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 48520.0,
      "end_time": 52500.0,
      "text": "want to understand, and put\nGrid into that situation."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 52500.0,
      "end_time": 55130.0,
      "text": "We'll use Grid on certain\nparts of the page,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 55130.0,
      "end_time": 57200.0,
      "text": "and not on other parts of the page."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 57200.0,
      "end_time": 59210.0,
      "text": "It's not like the tools\nthat we've been using,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 59210.0,
      "end_time": 63930.0,
      "text": "say, Bootstrap or Foundation,\nor 960 Grid, back in the day."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 63930.0,
      "end_time": 66590.0,
      "text": "It doesn't handle layout\nfor the whole page."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 66590.0,
      "end_time": 70170.0,
      "text": "It handles layout for\na particular container,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 70170.0,
      "end_time": 72570.0,
      "text": "one container on the page, and the items"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 72570.0,
      "end_time": 76210.0,
      "text": "that are directly, a direct\nchild of that container."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 76210.0,
      "end_time": 78280.0,
      "text": "So, you're gonna mix\nGrid with other things."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 78280.0,
      "end_time": 79600.0,
      "text": "You'll mix Grid with Flexbox."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 79600.0,
      "end_time": 81800.0,
      "text": "You'll mix Grid with a basic flow."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 81800.0,
      "end_time": 85630.0,
      "text": "You'll mix Grid with floats,\nwith other kinds of things."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 85630.0,
      "end_time": 88030.0,
      "text": "So, why do you wanna use Flexbox?"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 88030.0,
      "end_time": 90090.0,
      "text": "Why do you wanna use CSS Grid?"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 90090.0,
      "end_time": 91780.0,
      "text": "Which ones should you use when?"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 92960.0,
      "end_time": 95600.0,
      "text": "Flexbox is really great when you want to"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 95600.0,
      "end_time": 98200.0,
      "text": "line things up in one direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 98200.0,
      "end_time": 100520.0,
      "text": "Maybe you could think of it as"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 100520.0,
      "end_time": 103000.0,
      "text": "a whole bunch of boxes that are in an"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 103000.0,
      "end_time": 104960.0,
      "text": "infinitely long line."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 104960.0,
      "end_time": 107130.0,
      "text": "Oh, but it's not infinitely long."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 107130.0,
      "end_time": 109780.0,
      "text": "It's actually a limited amount of space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 109780.0,
      "end_time": 113360.0,
      "text": "so it happens to wrap, or doesn't wrap."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 113360.0,
      "end_time": 116160.0,
      "text": "Whether it wraps or not, the calculations"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 116160.0,
      "end_time": 118530.0,
      "text": "that are being made are all happening"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 118530.0,
      "end_time": 120130.0,
      "text": "one line at a time."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 120130.0,
      "end_time": 122820.0,
      "text": "The browser only ever thinks about things"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 122820.0,
      "end_time": 125360.0,
      "text": "in one dimension at a time."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 125360.0,
      "end_time": 127350.0,
      "text": "It doesn't have any way to know"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 127350.0,
      "end_time": 130060.0,
      "text": "if you happen, if you end up\nwith several different rows,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 130060.0,
      "end_time": 133470.0,
      "text": "it doesn't calculate\ninformation across those rows,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 133470.0,
      "end_time": 134700.0,
      "text": "or if you're going in the other direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 134700.0,
      "end_time": 136370.0,
      "text": "It will calculate them in one direction"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 136370.0,
      "end_time": 138290.0,
      "text": "and not in the other direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 138290.0,
      "end_time": 141250.0,
      "text": "Grid has the ability to line\nthings up in two directions."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 141250.0,
      "end_time": 143020.0,
      "text": "And in fact, Grid always wants to"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 143020.0,
      "end_time": 144670.0,
      "text": "line things up in two directions."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 144670.0,
      "end_time": 147170.0,
      "text": "You can't get it to\nkind of stagger things."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 147170.0,
      "end_time": 150300.0,
      "text": "It thinks about rows and\ncolumns at the same time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 150300.0,
      "end_time": 153500.0,
      "text": "and it's gonna wanna make\nadjustments to your grid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 153500.0,
      "end_time": 155250.0,
      "text": "based on what's going on in both of"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 155250.0,
      "end_time": 157200.0,
      "text": "those directions at the same time."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 157200.0,
      "end_time": 160440.0,
      "text": "So, here's a diagram of a layout that"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 160440.0,
      "end_time": 162130.0,
      "text": "you would do with Grid, where things"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 162130.0,
      "end_time": 165880.0,
      "text": "are actually lining up in both directions."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 165880.0,
      "end_time": 168120.0,
      "text": "And here's a diagram of how things"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 168120.0,
      "end_time": 170200.0,
      "text": "might work out in Flexbox, where the"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 170200.0,
      "end_time": 173200.0,
      "text": "calculations are being done in each row,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 173200.0,
      "end_time": 175720.0,
      "text": "one at a time with no\nregard to the other rows,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 175720.0,
      "end_time": 178580.0,
      "text": "and you can see that those\nthings don't actually line up."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 178580.0,
      "end_time": 180900.0,
      "text": "Perhaps, it's dependent on\nthe size of the content,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 180900.0,
      "end_time": 184840.0,
      "text": "or the size of the amount\nof stuff that's on the page."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 184840.0,
      "end_time": 186760.0,
      "text": "Here's a diagram that\nreally kind of shows you"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 186760.0,
      "end_time": 189690.0,
      "text": "what Grid is good at, and\nwhat Flexbox is good at."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 189690.0,
      "end_time": 191540.0,
      "text": "There are some situations where Flexbox"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 191540.0,
      "end_time": 193450.0,
      "text": "or Grid could be used,\nwhere they basically"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 193450.0,
      "end_time": 195350.0,
      "text": "do the same thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 195350.0,
      "end_time": 197650.0,
      "text": "One thing though, that Grid can do that"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 197650.0,
      "end_time": 201900.0,
      "text": "Flexbox cannot do, is\nintentionally overlap items."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 201900.0,
      "end_time": 203440.0,
      "text": "So if you're in a situation where maybe"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 203440.0,
      "end_time": 205110.0,
      "text": "either one would work, but you want to"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 205110.0,
      "end_time": 206590.0,
      "text": "overlap items, then that's gonna be"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 206590.0,
      "end_time": 210010.0,
      "text": "a situation you definitely\nwant to use Grid in."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 210010.0,
      "end_time": 212830.0,
      "text": "Here's an example where we've got"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 212830.0,
      "end_time": 214550.0,
      "text": "images that are content images,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 214550.0,
      "end_time": 216950.0,
      "text": "not background images,\nbut images in the content."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 216950.0,
      "end_time": 219800.0,
      "text": "And then, I've got a\nsentence for each one,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 219800.0,
      "end_time": 222140.0,
      "text": "and a little background colour\non each of those sentences."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 222140.0,
      "end_time": 223520.0,
      "text": "The sentences are different lengths,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 223520.0,
      "end_time": 225880.0,
      "text": "so we don't wanna use some\nsort of absolute positioning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 225880.0,
      "end_time": 227090.0,
      "text": "or something that's not gonna work"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 227090.0,
      "end_time": 228550.0,
      "text": "for different amounts of content."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 228550.0,
      "end_time": 229551.0,
      "text": "We're gonna use Grid for this."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 229551.0,
      "end_time": 232550.0,
      "text": "But we're using Grid,\nwe could use Flexbox,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 232550.0,
      "end_time": 234890.0,
      "text": "if there's no overlap, but\nbecause there's overlap,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 234890.0,
      "end_time": 236700.0,
      "text": "we wanna use Grid in this situation."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 236700.0,
      "end_time": 239160.0,
      "text": "So, get to know Grid, get to know Flexbox."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 239160.0,
      "end_time": 241140.0,
      "text": "Kind of know what each one is best at,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 241140.0,
      "end_time": 243080.0,
      "text": "and then use whichever one is best."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 243080.0,
      "end_time": 246200.0,
      "text": "It depends on which one\nhas the super powers"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 246200.0,
      "end_time": 248210.0,
      "text": "that you need at that moment."
    }
  ]
}